&lt;p&gt;The Royal Marsden Hospital has an international reputation for high quality patient care, education and research. Its partnership with the Institute of Cancer Research has created the largest comprehensive cancer centre in Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Marsden NHS Trust is based on two sites (117 inpatient beds at Fulham Road, Chelsea and 89 inpatient beds at Downs Road, Sutton, Surrey), both devoted exclusively to the diagnosis, treatment and study of all forms of cancer and related disorders. The Royal Marsden NHS Trust’s work is closely allied with that of the Institute of Cancer Research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Royal Marsden Hospital is inviting applicants for a medical oncology clinical fellow. This clinical post will involve working under supervision of the consultants within &lt;/strong&gt;GI &lt;strong&gt;medical oncology team based in Chelsea in conjunction with the multidisciplinary teams to deliver services to patients, lead on innovative teaching programs, deliver quality improvement projects and initiate new clinical research.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a fixed term 6 month post which is particularly suitable for a Doctor who seeks to enhance their knowledge and skills in complex &lt;/strong&gt;GI &lt;strong&gt;cancer patients. Please see job description for more details and example job plan.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will have the opportunity to join the general medical oncology on-call SpR rota.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lucy McManus, Deputy CBU manager, lucy.mcmanus@rmh.nhs.uk, 020 7352 8171 EXT 1675&lt;/p&gt;
